  "text": "Depressive symptoms during pregnancy and postpartum were measured using the Edinburgh Postnatal Depression Scale [EPDS; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . EPDS includes 10 items, which are measured on a 4-point Likert scale, and results in a possible total score range from 0 to 30. EPDS was used to measure depressive symptoms over the 7 days prior to the interview. The validity and reliability of the EPDS were demonstrated among immigrant and native-born women in Taiwan [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The internal consistency of the scale, using Cronbach's alpha, was 0.916 (0.918 for immigrant women and 0.913 for native-born women) at postpartum. We used a cutoff Table 1 . Factor analysis for the domestic decision-making power scale (N = 407).",
